bib.title: (3He,t) reactions on the T=1 nuclei 18O, 22Ne, 26Mg and 30Si.

free_txt: For 15.4 and 16 MeV data.
For 30 MeV data.
A system of four Si surface barrier counter
telescopes (dE~400 mu-m, E~1500 mu-m) was used.
The telescope which usually stood in the forward
direction was fitted with smaller slits than the other
telescopes in order to reduce the counting rate. It was
equipped with two dE counters which together had a
total thickness of 600 mu-m so that only protons,
deuterons and tritons reached the E-counters.

Targets of less than 100 mu-g/cm2 were used.
The normalization of the reaction cross section was
done by fitting the 6 MeV 3He elastic scattering data
with an optical-model calculated reaction cross section
for reaction angles between 20 and 30 degr. where the
cross section differs from the Rutherford cross section
by less than 10% for any reasonable potential
parameters.
Tangsten oxide targets on carbon backings were produced
through oxidation of tangsten foils in an 18O
atmosphere.

A special gas target was constructed for 22Ne according
to the principle of the sandwich target with natural
nickel foil entrance and exit windows of 280 mu-g/cm2
and 700 mu-g/cm2, respectively. The gas pressure was
approximately 100 Torr.
